## Interaction Contract

- `variant` wins over semantic `type`; when `variant` is absent, `type="text"` maps to the `ghost` variant and other semantic types map to their matching variants.
- Size aliases normalize to `sm`, `md`, and `lg`; `large` maps to `lg`, while `small` and `mini` map to `sm`.
- `disabled` and `loading` both disable the native `<button>` and suppress the emitted `click` event.
- `loadingVariant="bar"` is only visible for `block` buttons; icon-only / inline buttons use the spinner slot or overlay spinner.
- Non-block, non-circle buttons animate loading width changes with a size FLIP transition.
- `TxSplitButton` disables both action zones while loading; `menuDisabled` only disables the menu trigger.

## Best Practices

- Keep one primary action per view or card. Pair `primary` with `ghost` or `secondary` for lower-priority actions.
- Use `nativeType="submit"` only inside forms; the default `button` prevents accidental form submission.
- Use `loading` for every async action and clear it on success and failure paths so the button cannot get stuck disabled.
- Prefer `circle` only for icon-only actions; when `block` and `circle` are combined, the component intentionally keeps regular label layout.
- Use `loadingVariant="bar"` for full-width submit bars and keep spinner loading for compact or icon buttons.
- Keep menu actions in `TxSplitButton` responsible for calling the provided `close()` callback after a selection.


## Review Notes

- Reviewed against `packages/tuffex/packages/components/src/button/src/button.vue`, `split-button.vue`, `types.ts`, `split-button.ts`, and both button test files.
- **Verified coverage:** `button.test.ts` covers label rendering, semantic type mapping, variant precedence, size aliases, disabled/loading click suppression, loading bar behavior, icons, shape classes, borderless mode, and native type; `split-button.test.ts` covers menu rendering, primary click, disabled/loading suppression, and `menuOpenChange`.
- Accessibility note: the native button handles base keyboard activation. For icon-only or `circle` buttons, provide an external accessible label through surrounding markup or attrs where the visual icon is not self-explanatory.

